Another myth I must debunk.  FASA had full rights to use the Macross art for its Battledroids game (which later became Battletech).  They had a licensing agreement with Harmony Gold. Everything was all neat on a piece of paper with signatures.  All was cool.  FASA was using the art totally and completely legally.<br>
<br>
Then, Harmony Gold decided they didn't want FASA using the art--15 or so years later.  FASA had every right to take the case to court, but, as a relatively small company, they would run out of money long before the case was ever decided.  Harmony Gold could last much longer than FASA.<br>
<br>
